
msgid "Lua-YAML prettier multiline output"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The ``lua-yaml`` encoder selects the string style automatically, but in "
"Tarantool context, it can be beneficial to enforce them, for example, for "
"better readability. The ``yaml_pretty_multiline`` compat option allows to "
"encode multiline strings in a block style."
msgstr ""

msgid "Old and new behavior"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The ``compat`` module allows you to chose between the ``lua-yaml`` encodes "
"multiline strings as usual or in the enforced block scalar style:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"tarantool> compat.yaml_pretty_multiline = 'old'\n"
"---\n"
"...\n"
"\n"
"tarantool> return \"Title: xxx\\n- Item 1\\n- Item 2\\n\"\n"
"---\n"
"- 'Title: xxx\n"
"\n"
"  - Item 1\n"
"\n"
"  - Item 2\n"
"\n"
"  '\n"
"...\n"
"\n"
"tarantool> compat.yaml_pretty_multiline = 'new'\n"
"---\n"
"...\n"
"\n"
"tarantool> return \"Title: xxx\\n- Item 1\\n- Item 2\\n\"\n"
"---\n"
"- |\n"
"  Title: xxx\n"
"  - Item 1\n"
"  - Item 2\n"
"..."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"You can select the new/old behavior in ``compat``. It affects the global "
"YAML encoder."
msgstr ""

